### Know What to Avoid

![Image](/lot/asset/page/article/a-password-you-can-remember/19856614.jpg)
 Photo by [Markus Winkler][1] from [Pexels][2].

Before figuring out what you want to put in your password, here are a few things that you shouldn’t put in your
password:

 - Pet, family, or friend names
 - Words as they appear in the dictionary (e.g., “c@stl3” is fine, while “castle” is not)
 - Personal information (e.g., your phone number)
 - Public information (e.g., something having to do with your easily researched extracurricular activities)
 - Acronyms.

