### Consider Common Password Strategies

![Image](/lot/asset/page/article/a-password-you-can-remember/5425637.jpg)
 Photo by [Anna Tarazevich][5] from [Pexels][6].

If you don’t have your own method of creating a memorable password, you might want to try one of the following:

 - Removing the vowels from a word or phrase (e.g., “Hello darkness my old friend” becomes “hlldrknssmldfrnd”).
 - Shifting your hands when typing (for example, using the motion that you’d use to type “wikiHow” with your hands
   shifted down one row on the keyboard).
 - Using a cipher (e.g., a page number, paragraph line, and word from a book).
 - Doubling your password (e.g., creating a password, typing a space or a separating character, and retyping the
   password).

