### Add an Abbreviation for Your Password’s Service

![Image](/lot/asset/page/article/a-password-you-can-remember/1289845.jpg)
 Photo by [Magda Ehlers][15] from [Pexels][16].

For example, if the password is for your work email address, you might add “work email” (or “wrk ml”, etc.) to the end
of the password. This way, you can use the same base password for most services without repeating the exact password
anywhere.

 - It’s incredibly important not to repeat your password more than once (e.g., don’t use your Facebook password for your
   email account, etc.).

