### Create Variations of Your Password

![Image](/lot/asset/page/article/a-password-you-can-remember/6990399.jpg)
 Photo by [DS Stories][19] from [Pexels][20].

While adding an abbreviation to the end of your password will help you remember a specific service’s password, you’ll
eventually need to change your passwords altogether. If you’re happy with your current password, try typing the password
while holding down the ⇧ Shift key, or capitalize random letters.

 - If you replaced any letters with numbers, you might switch back to using letters and use numbers for different
   letters in the password.

